\pard\plain \ri0\sl240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0 The original external problem is solved at the same time and in the same scene in this story.  This isn't always the case; often the story's turning point is the resolution of the inner problem, and the solution of the outer problem depends on the protagonist's change.  We should state the resolution of the external problem.  Clicking on the first problem from the list at the left of the screen, and then on the }{\f3\fs24\b1\i0 Resolution}{\f2\fs24\b0\i0  tab, allows us to key this information:}
\par\plain \f2\fs24\b0\i0
\par\pard\plain \tx-720\ri0\sl240\slmult0\qj\ltrch\loch \f2\fs20\b0\i0
