\par\pard\plain \tx-720\ri0\sl-1\slmult0\qj\ltrch\loch {\f4\fs24\b0\i0 5}
\par\pard\plain \ri0\sl240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch \f2\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f2\fs24\b0\i0 The copy function populated the }{\f3\fs24\b1\i0 Plots }{\f2\fs24\b0\i0 form with a series of plot points which suggest where in the dramatic progression of a story certain things should happen.  The }{\f3\fs24\b1\i0 Notes}{\f2\fs24\b0\i0  tabs on these plot points contain some suggestions.  For example, the notes for 'Narrative hook' read:}
\par\plain \f2\fs24\b0\i0
\par\pard\plain \tx-720\li720\ri0\sl240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0 It's important to capture the reader's interest at the beginning of the story sufficiently to keep him reading until the story itself (the protagonist and the problem) have engaged his attention.  The opening paragraphs of the story must serve as an advertisement that it's worth reading.}
\par\plain \f1\fs24\b0\i0}